   <mods:abstract>Has sent Essex to stay with Jay. "His attachment to Mr. Ireland and the
            improper use that gentleman made of it" caused his opposition to Jay's proposal to stay
            with him. Essex received very poor instruction at Mr. Ireland's. Mr. Holker has taken
            out letters in Pennsylvania. There is a large debt in Philadelphia to be recovered.
            Measures must be taken to prevent its falling into Holker's hands. Mr. Chase is
            Catherine's only confidante. Many have offered to help, but their motives are not
            good.</mods:abstract>
